---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing AR — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing AR with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AR words for your next winning play."
  keywords="scrabble words containing ar, ar words scrabble, words with ar, scrabble ar word list, ar scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing AR — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing AR with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AR words for your next winning play.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-ar" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest-scoring AR words?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top AR words include BIZARRE (18 pts), QUARRY (18 pts), SPARKLE (13 pts), MARKET (12 pts), CHARM (12 pts), and JAR (10 pts). AR pairs especially well with high-value tiles like Z, Q, and J." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many Scrabble words contain AR?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 1,100 valid Scrabble words contain AR, making it one of the most common pairs. It appears in words of every length and position, giving maximum flexibility." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What short AR words are essential?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Key short AR words: BAR (5 pts), CAR (5 pts), FAR (6 pts), JAR (10 pts), TAR (3 pts), WAR (6 pts), ARC (5 pts), ARK (7 pts), and ARM (5 pts). JAR and ARK score highest in this group." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing AR — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">AR is one of the most productive letter pairs in Scrabble, appearing in well over a thousand valid words. From short tactical plays like BAR, CAR, and JAR to longer scoring words like SPARKLE and BIZARRE, the AR combination is a workhorse. The pair works equally well at the start (ART, ARM), middle (CARD, MARKET), and end (STAR, GUITAR) of words.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top AR Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BIZARRE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Very strange</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUARRY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An open excavation</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SPARKLE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To glitter</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MARKET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A trading place</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHARM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">An appeal</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JAR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A glass container</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHART</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A visual diagram</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GUARD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To protect</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">STAR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A celestial body</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BAR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A long rod</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ART</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Creative expression</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,100+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid AR words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Very Common</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair rarity</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The -AR Ending Arsenal</h2>

      <p>The -AR ending creates a huge family of words. BAR, CAR, FAR, JAR, TAR, WAR, and STAR give you plays in any tight position, while longer -AR words like GUITAR and CELLAR score well.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHARM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AR is a <span class="text-white font-medium">top-tier utility pair</span> with 1,100+ valid words. JAR (10 pts) leads short AR words with the 8-point J. For longer plays, BIZARRE (18 pts) and QUARRY (18 pts) deliver huge scores. The -AR ending gives you reliable 3-letter options in any board state.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every AR word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>